            . I am an officer of Hatton Garden office. I apprehended the prisoner on suspicion of an other robbery; I found the duplicate of a shirt at his mother's lodgings; this is the duplicate.</p>
               <p>Hart. I delivered that duplicate to the prisoner for this shirt.</p>
               <p>The property produced and identified.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The shirt that I pledged was my own shirt; I bought the shirt on the 12th in Petticoat lane; I was distressed for money, I pledged it on the 13th.</p>
